title: Google\Cloud\GkeHub\V1beta1\KubernetesMetadata
name: KubernetesMetadata
description:
KubernetesMetadata provides informational metadata for Memberships representing Kubernetes clusters.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.gkehub.v1beta1.KubernetesMetadata

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.kubernetes_api_server_version
params.description: Output only. Kubernetes API server version string as reported by '/version'.

params.name: data.node_provider_id
params.description: Output only. Node providerID as reported by the first node in the list of nodes on the Kubernetes endpoint. On Kubernetes platforms that support zero-node clusters (like GKE-on-GCP), the node_count will be zero and the node_provider_id will be empty.

params.name: data.node_count
params.description: Output only. Node count as reported by Kubernetes nodes resources.

params.name: data.vcpu_count
params.description: Output only. vCPU count as reported by Kubernetes nodes resources.

params.name: data.memory_mb
params.description: Output only. The total memory capacity as reported by the sum of all Kubernetes nodes resources, defined in MB.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Output only. The time at which these details were last updated. This update_time is different from the Membership-level update_time since EndpointDetails are updated internally for API consumers.
